Subject: [PATCH] =?UTF-8?q?feat:=20user=20management=20=E2=80=94=20bulk=20?=
 =?UTF-8?q?create,=20class/section=20filter=20for=20parents,=20bulk=20rese?=
 =?UTF-8?q?t,=20export=20credentials=20to=20Excel/PDF?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Four additions to the User Login Management page:

1. "Create Missing Logins" button at the page header.
   POST /school/users/create-missing accepts {type: 'parent'|'student'|'all'}
   and creates User rows for any StudentParent / Student records that
   don't have one yet, with the same defaults as portal:create-users
   (parents: parent123, students: DOB or student123). Returns the new
   credentials so the admin can immediately export them. A small badge
   in the header shows how many parents/students are still missing
   accounts.

2. Class + Section filter now applies to parents too (previously
   student-only). For parents the filter joins through their children's
   currentAcademicHistory. Section dropdown is class-scoped.

3. Bulk password reset. Each row now has a checkbox; a sticky bar
   appears when anything is selected. POST /school/users/bulk-reset
   resets every selected user to a fresh 10-char random password and
   returns the new credentials.

4. Export. Both flows above hand the credentials to a new modal that
   exposes Excel + PDF download buttons. POST /school/users/export-
   credentials posts the rows back, server returns the file:
   - Excel via maatwebsite/excel (UserCredentialsExport)
   - PDF via barryvdh/laravel-dompdf using a new
     resources/views/exports/user-credentials.blade.php

   Server never persists plaintext passwords. The modal is one-shot
   ("shown only once") with a confidentiality warning. All bulk
   actions are logged (admin id, count, timestamp — never the
   passwords themselves).

Routes added in routes/web.php under the existing /school/users group:
  POST users/create-missing      → users.create-missing
  POST users/bulk-reset          → users.bulk-reset
  POST users/export-credentials  → users.export-credentials

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>
